<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Method limit() of Oracle add an extra field "zend_db_rownum". This field is positioned at the beginning of the result.</p>

<p>In case of using fetchCol(), we return the value of "zend_db_rownum" instead of the desired field.</p>

<p>We can reverse in Zend_Db_Adapter_Oracle::limit():</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
SELECT ROWNUM AS zend_db_rownum, z1.*
</code></pre>

<p>should be</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
SELECT z1.*, ROWNUM AS zend_db_rownum
</code></pre>

